***Sympathizes With Nigerlites Over Insecurity MINNA – The former Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has visited former President General Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida (IBB) and also held closed door meeting with his host at his hilltop residence, Minna, Niger state capital. Former Vice President Atiku Abubarkar is the second 2023 Presidential aspirant to visit IBB to solicit his support after their former Lagos state Governor and leader of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC), Asiwaju Ahmed Bola Tinubu. Ekiti Governorship Election: Kolawole Receives Certificate Of… Bye-Election: Alade Olanrewaju Lawson Wins APC Primary Though details of the meeting which lasted for close to an hour was not made known, but feelers had it that the meeting may not be unconnected with the Presidential intents of the former Vice President whom it was gathered is consulting widely against the popular belief that the south should produce successor to President Muhammadu Buhari. Atiku Abubarkar also later paid courtesy visit on the Niger state Governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Bello to sympathize with the government and people of the state over incessant attacks and killing by combined forces of; Armed Bandits, Boko-Haram and ISWAP. In an interview, former Vice President Atiku Abubarkar told journalists that he was at the Niger state Government house on a courtesy visit to sympathize with the state government over prevailing security challenges facing the state. Former Vice President Atiku who however kept sealed slips over his 2023 aspirations simply said, ‘my aspiration for 2023 will be made public when the time comes’.